  <prompt>
    Extend `WorkspaceLayoutDto` with `modifiedOn: DateTimeOffset`, mapped from the Dataverse `modifiedon`
    column (or rowversion derivative). Update `WorkspaceLayoutEndpoints.cs` mapping to emit the field.
    Update the frontend TypeScript type to receive it. Update the Manage Workspaces pane to render the date
    for each layout. Record §10 Placement Justification in PR notes. Verify publish-size ≤60 MB.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior .NET 8 Minimal API developer with React/TypeScript fluency. Familiar with Dataverse SDK +
    `WorkspaceLayoutService.cs` mapping patterns. Bias toward additive, low-blast-radius changes: this is
    a DTO field extension, not a service redesign.
  </role>

  <goal>
    (a) `WorkspaceLayoutDto` in `Api/Workspace/WorkspaceLayoutDtos.cs` has a `ModifiedOn: DateTimeOffset`
    property; (b) `WorkspaceLayoutService.cs` populates it from the Dataverse entity's `modifiedon`
    attribute; (c) `WorkspaceLayoutEndpoints.cs` emits the new field via the existing mapping; (d) frontend
    TS type (in shared lib OR SpaarkeAi types file) includes `modifiedOn: string` (ISO-8601); (e)
    `ManageWorkspacesPane.tsx` renders the date for each layout (per FR-07 acceptance); (f) CLAUDE.md §10
    Placement Justification entry in PR notes; (g) `dotnet publish` ≤60 MB compressed verified.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec FR-07 (B-4) + plan §4 Phase 5: the Manage Workspaces pane currently shows layout name and
      owner but NOT when each layout was last modified — making it hard for operators to know which
      layouts are stale. Dataverse already maintains `modifiedon` per record; the BFF just needs to surface
      it via the existing DTO + endpoint. This is a small additive change but is part of the §10
      governance scope (B-5 will use this same DTO surface to add ETag concurrency support). NFR-01
      publish-size: must verify ≤60 MB compressed after server change.
    </background>
