  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Rigor declaration">Output rigor declaration: 🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL — bff-api tag, modifies .cs DTO + endpoint mapping + frontend types, §10 Placement Justification REQUIRED. Step 9.5 quality gates MANDATORY.</step>
    <step order="1" name="Confirm file locations">Re-confirm file paths at task start: `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Workspace/WorkspaceLayoutDtos.cs`, `WorkspaceLayoutEndpoints.cs`, `Services/Workspace/WorkspaceLayoutService.cs`. Confirm frontend Manage pane location (likely `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/workspace/ManageWorkspacesPane.tsx` — verify the actual filename) and TS type location.</step>
    <step order="2" name="§10 Placement Justification">Draft Placement Justification per `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` decision criteria. Stash in PR notes: this is a CRUD-side DTO extension; no AI coupling; in-process is correct per ADR-013 (no service change anyway).</step>
    <step order="3" name="Extend DTO">Add `ModifiedOn` property of type `DateTimeOffset` to `WorkspaceLayoutDto`. Match the existing property style (record positional vs class get-init — match what's there). Include XML doc comment citing FR-07.</step>
    <step order="4" name="Extend service mapping">Update `WorkspaceLayoutService.cs` to map the Dataverse `modifiedon` attribute to the DTO. (Dataverse `modifiedon` is typically `DateTime` UTC — convert to `DateTimeOffset` with `DateTimeOffset.SpecifyKind(value, DateTimeKind.Utc)` or `new DateTimeOffset(value, TimeSpan.Zero)`.)</step>
    <step order="5" name="Update integration tests">Edit `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Integration/Workspace/WorkspaceLayoutEndpointTests.cs` to assert the new field is present, non-null, and ISO-8601 serializable on the wire. Seed test fixtures with `modifiedon` values.</step>
    <step order="6" name="Update frontend TS type">Locate the frontend `WorkspaceLayout` type — likely in `src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/types/` (consolidated by task 051) OR in SpaarkeAi local types. Add `modifiedOn: string` (ISO-8601 from wire). Update any type-guard / parseLayoutJson logic to pass through the new field.</step>
    <step order="7" name="Render in Manage pane">Edit `ManageWorkspacesPane.tsx` to add a "Modified" column / line showing each layout's `modifiedOn`. Use Fluent UI v9 date formatting OR `Intl.DateTimeFormat(navigator.language, { dateStyle: 'short' })` — no hardcoded date format. New layouts (just created) MUST show "just now" or near-equivalent relative time (per FR-07 acceptance).</step>
    <step order="8" name="Build verification (server)">Run `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/`. Verify 0 errors / 0 new warnings. Run `dotnet test --filter "FullyQualifiedName~WorkspaceLayout"`. Verify all pass.</step>
    <step order="9" name="Build verification (client)">Run `npm run build` in SpaarkeAi (and `@spaarke/ai-widgets` if types were modified there). Verify 0 errors. `tsc --noEmit` clean.</step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality gates">Invoke `code-review` skill and `adr-check` skill. Verify §10 BFF hygiene enforcement passes (skills updated 2026-05-21).</step>
    <step order="10" name="Publish-size check (NFR-01)">Run `dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/`. Verify compressed publish size ≤60 MB. Record delta vs baseline in PR notes.</step>
    <step order="11" name="CVE check (NFR-09)">Run `dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive`. Verify 0 new HIGH-severity findings.</step>
    <step order="12" name="Deploy">Deploy BFF via `bff-deploy` skill. Deploy SpaarkeAi via `code-page-deploy` skill (Manage pane is in SpaarkeAi).</step>
    <step order="13" name="Smoke verification">Open SpaarkeAi → Manage Workspaces pane → verify each layout shows a "Modified" date. Create a new layout → verify it shows "just now" or near-equivalent.</step>
    <step order="14" name="Update TASK-INDEX">Edit `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: flip task 053 status 🔲 → ✅. Mark task 054 (B-5) as ready.</step>
    <step order="15" name="Document deviations">If any deviation (e.g., the Dataverse `modifiedon` mapping required a custom converter, or the frontend type was in an unexpected location), record in `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/notes/`.</step>
  </steps>

