    §10 Placement Justification (for PR notes):
      - Decision-criteria answers per .claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md:
        (1) Latency budget against BFF state → YES (workspace layout list is the cold-load path).
        (2) Writes BFF-managed session/audit/safety state → YES (Dataverse sprk_workspacelayout).
        (3) Retroactive annotation of streaming response → N/A.
        (4) Event-driven, no sync user wait → NO.
        (5) Thin facade to external consumers → NO.
      - 3 "BFF" answers; placement correct. Additive DTO field only — zero new endpoints / services / DI
        registrations / NuGet packages. No new CRUD→AI dep. Endpoint surface unchanged. ADR-008 filter
        pipeline unchanged. Publish-size delta ≈ 0 (one DateTimeOffset field).

    Hooks left for task 054 (B-5):
      - Server-side: `ModifiedOn` is on the wire; B-5 can use it directly as the ETag strong validator.
        B-5 may want to re-read after Create/Update to obtain the canonical Dataverse rowversion (the
        synthesized DTOs use DateTimeOffset.UtcNow as a placeholder for clarity — see Create/Update remarks
        in WorkspaceLayoutService.cs). For ETag generation, an RFC 7232 strong validator like
        `"W/\"{ticks}\""` or `"\"{base64(modifiedOn)}\""` against the persisted timestamp is recommended.
      - Client-side: `modifiedOn` is already on the TS type; client code that sends If-Match can read
        it directly from the cached layout. The MutationAuth payload in workspaceLayoutMutations.ts
        does NOT currently echo modifiedOn — B-5 will likely add an `ifMatch?: string` option to the
        Update payload helpers.
      - Sentinel handling: hard-coded system layouts emit the Unix-epoch sentinel. B-5 should treat
        system layouts (isSystem=true) as not-concurrency-controlled rather than synthesizing an ETag
        from the sentinel (system layouts already reject PUT/DELETE with 403).

    Quality gates (Step 9.5): self-review pass — no ADR violations; CLAUDE.md §10 satisfied; ADRs 001 /
